==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perspicuity
<hw>Per`spi*cu"i*ty</hw>
<pr>(p⟦etil⟧r`sp⟦icr⟧*k⟦umac⟧"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perspicuitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>perspicuit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being transparent or
translucent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality of being perspicuous to the
understanding; clearness of expression or thought.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Sagacity; perspicacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Clearness; perspicuousness; plainness;
distinctness; lucidity; transparency. See <er>Clearness</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perspicuous</ent>⟦br⟧
